Type: Bacterial Infection
Cause: food contaminated with the bacterium Listeria monocytogenes.
Symptoms: headache, stiff neck, confusion, loss of balance, and convulsions in addition to fever and muscle aches.
Incubation period:1 to 4 weeks after eating food contaminated with Listeria.
Prevention: All meat should be properly cooked. Refrigerate or freeze cooked foods within two hours of preparation. All milk products should be made with pasteurized milk to minimize the risk of contaminating food.